<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2015/02/09/springone2gx-2014-replay-restful-grails-2">SpringOne2GX 2014 Replay: RESTful Grails 2</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon news-and-events"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/news">News and Events</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/c910c2f6520a5977a836d74e86e07cb4?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<span class="author">Pieter Humphrey</span>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2015-02-09 22:55:00.0">February 9, 2015</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="1963" href="/blog/2015/02/09/springone2gx-2014-replay-restful-grails-2#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Recorded at SpringOne2GX 2014. </p>
<p>Speaker: Jeff Scott Brown </p>
<p>Essential Grails Track </p>
<p>Slides: <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/SpringCentral/res-tful-grails2">http://www.slideshare.net/SpringCentral/res-tful-grails2</a> </p>
<p>Grails 2 includes a lot of features and functionality related to building RESTful services. These include an entirely new and more flexibile data binding system, runtime and compile time metaprogramming which greatly reduce the amount of code required in your RESTful services, a rich set of content negotiation tools and more.</p>
<p> <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/8xYi9n0pYFs" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe> </p>
<p><iframe width="560" height="315" src="" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>
</div>
</section>
